these quick'n'dirty scripts lets you see how many single-copy genes are found in a given fasta file
according to different curated databases.

say you have your contigs.fa.

if you run this:

    anvi-script-gen_stats_for_single_copy_genes.sh contigs.fa

you should get a PDF that looks like this:

    https://i.imgur.com/2oPU849.png
